          <title>MLB study: Velocity, max efforts likely causing pitching injuries; rule changes should be considered</title>
          <description><![CDATA[NEW YORK (AP) — A yearlong study by Major League Baseball concluded rising velocities, pitch shaping and emphasis on maximum effort are the likely causes of the vast increase in pitcher injuries and recommended exploring rules changes to address the problem.]]></description>
